        "text": "Summarizing what I wrote, I see Illich's use of the term \"conviviality\" as technical jargon: the use of a common-language term in a highly context-specific meaning that is not obvious to outsiders. Personally, as an interdisciplinary academic, I am used to dealing with technical jargon, but I guess most people are not.",
